h3. What problem are you facing?

Callback is called twice when an error occurs when using "insertOne". I suspect it'll affect all collection APIs.
h3. What driver and relevant dependency versions are you using?

MongoDB driver 4.1.3.

Database version 4.4.8
h3. Steps to reproduce?

Call "insertOne" after connection has been closed to force an error - notice that the callback is executed twice. I believe the error is here:

drivers\node-mongodb-native\collection.js

Line 214:
{code:java}
} catch (error) {
 // Collection operation may throw because of max bson size, catch it here
 // See gh-3906
 if (typeof callback === 'function') {
     callback(error); <-- THIS SHOULD RETURN
 } else {
     this.conn.emit('operation-end', { _id: opId, modelName: _this.modelName, collectionName: this.name, method: i, error: error });
 }
 if (typeof lastArg === 'function') {
     lastArg(error); <-- THIS CALLS THE CB AGAIN
 } else {
     throw error;
 }
}{code}
Higher up the file (line 162) you can see that the "callback" already calls "lastArg":
{code:java}
callback = function collectionOperationCallback(err, res) {
  if (err != null) {
    _this.conn.emit('operation-end', { _id: opId, modelName: _this.modelName, collectionName: _this.name, method: i, error: err });
  } else {
    _this.conn.emit('operation-end', { _id: opId, modelName: _this.modelName, collectionName: _this.name, method: i, result: res });
  }
  return lastArg.apply(this, arguments); <-- ALREADY CALLS LASTARG
};
{code}

The first clause in the wake function will prevent the task from being run with the intention being to prevent extremely frequent repeated calls. Since lastWakeTime is updated on every call to wake then the gap between lastWakeTime and currentTime might never grow.

{code:javascript}
const currentTime = clock();
const timeSinceLastWake = currentTime - lastWakeTime;
lastWakeTime = currentTime;

if (timeSinceLastWake < minInterval) {
  return;
}
{code}
